No further substantive feedback.

The round-2 consistency concerns are resolved in the current draft:

- Chapter 09 now cleanly separates `v1` from full `v0 conformance`, and unqualified `v0 conformance` is reserved for the final level.
- The composite-commit section now correctly distinguishes the real `05 §2.2` cases from the non-composite `eval_error` control case.
- The plugin marker text matches the leveled-claim model.
- The in-scope summary now matches the actual subscribe-reconnect at-least-once test.

This looks ready to move to implementation.
